  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail profile picture, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Gmail:**\n   - Go to [gmail.com](https://mail.google.com) and log in with your Google account.\n\n2. **Access Google Account Management:**\n   - Click on your profile picture located in the top-right corner of the Gmail interface.\n   - In the drop-down menu, click on \"Manage your Google Account.\"\n\n3. **Navigate to Personal Info:**\n   - In the left-hand menu, click on \"Personal info.\"\n\n4. **Change Profile Picture:**\n   - Under the \"Profile\" section, you should see your current profile picture.\n   - Click on the profile picture.\n\n5. **Remove Profile Picture:**\n   - You should see options to change or remove your profile picture.\n   - Click on the \"Remove\" option.\n\nAfter completing these steps, your profile picture should be removed, and your account will revert to displaying the default avatar.\n\nNote that it may take some time for this change to propagate across all Google services.",
